---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import HelpCallout from "../../components/HelpCallout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="What is gambling?"
  description="Gambling means risking something of value on an uncertain outcome. Here are the common forms and how access has changed."
>
  <header class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="page-header__eyebrow">
        <a href="/understand-gambling">← Understand gambling</a>
      </p>
      <h1>What is gambling?</h1>
      <p class="page-header__lead">
        Gambling means risking something of value — usually money — on an
        uncertain outcome, hoping to win more. Most adults who gamble do not
        experience harm, but knowing the forms helps you understand the risks.
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <h2>Common forms of gambling</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Lottery and scratch tickets</strong></li>
        <li><strong>Casino games</strong> — slot machines, table games like blackjack and roulette</li>
        <li><strong>Sports betting</strong> — in person and on phones and apps</li>
        <li><strong>Online casino and poker</strong></li>
        <li><strong>Charitable gaming</strong> — bingo, raffles, pull-tabs</li>
        <li><strong>Horse and dog racing</strong> (parimutuel wagering)</li>
        <li><strong>Daily fantasy sports</strong></li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Not all gambling looks like a casino. Buying scratch tickets, betting on a
        game with an app, or opening a paid "loot box" in a video game are all
        forms of risking money on chance.
      </p>

      <h2>How access has changed</h2>
      <p>
        Gambling used to mean going somewhere — a casino, a track, a store. Today a
        phone can be a 24-hour gambling device. Since 2018, legal sports betting has
        expanded to many states, and online betting has grown quickly. More access
        and more advertising mean more chances to gamble — and more chances for
        gambling to become harmful.
      </p>

      <h2>What's legal where you live</h2>
      <p>
        The forms of gambling that are legal, and who regulates them, vary by state
        and territory. See <a href="/find-your-state">your state or territory</a>
        for the local picture.
      </p>

      <HelpCallout />

      <div class="sources">
        <h2>Learn more</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://www.ncpgambling.org/">National Council on Problem Gambling</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
